    {
      "question": "If 5 cosh x + 4 sinh x = 5, then what is the value of e^x?",
      "difficulty": "hard",
      "hasDiagram": false,
      "options": {
        "A": "3",
        "B": "1",
        "C": "1/3",
        "D": "5"
      },
      "answer": "B",
      "hint": "Express cosh and sinh in terms of e^x.",
      "solution": "5(e^x + e^-x)/2 + 4(e^x - e^-x)/2 = 5 -> 9e^x + e^-x = 10 -> 9(e^x)^2 - 10(e^x) + 1 = 0 -> e^x = 1 or 1/9. If options have 1, B is correct.",
      "id": 10
    },
